quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  27,67,"And those who disbelieve say: when we have become dust, we and our fathers, shall we, for sooth, be brought forth"
  27,68,"Assuredly we have been promised this aforetime, we and our fathers. Naught is this but fables of the ancients"
  27,69,"Say thou: travel in the land and behold what like hath been the end of the culprits"
  27,70,And grieve thou not over them nor be straitened because of that which they plot
  27,71,"And they say: when will this Promise be fufilled if ye say sooth"
  27,72,"Say thou: belike close behind you may be some of that which ye would hasten on"
  27,73,"And verily thine Lord is full of grace for mankind, but most of them give not thanks"
  27,74,And verily thine Lord knoweth whatsoever their breasts conceal and whatsoever they make known
  27,75,And naught there is hidden in the heaven or the earth but it is in a Manifest Book
  27,76,Verily this Qur'an recounteth with truth unto the Children of Isra'il much of that wherein they differ
  27,77,And verily it is a guidance and a mercy unto the believers
  27,78,"And verily thine Lord shall decide between them with His judgment, and He is the Mighty, the Knowing"
  27,79,Wherefore put thy trust in Allah; verily thou art on manifest truth
  27,80,"Verily thou canst not make the dead hear, nor canst thou make the deaf hear the call when they flee turning their backs"
  27,81,Nor canst thou lead the blind out of their error. Thou canst make none hear save these who believe in Our signs and who have submitted themselves
  27,82,"And when the word shall come to be fulfilled concerning them, We shall bring forth a beast of the earth speaking unto them, that the people have not of Our signs been convinced"